jcr:content.jcr:title: UNDERSTAND
jcr:content.jcr:description: Contrary to popular belief, Saudi Arabia has four distinct seasons and a climate that varies between regions. Read on for a seasonal overview of the Kingdom’s weather.

jcr:content.jcr:title: Language and Culture
jcr:content.jcr:description: Arabic is the official language of Saudi Arabia and the primary language used in all dealings and public transactions. Saudi Arabia’s rich heritage and traditions have been shaped by its position as a historic trade hub and the birthplace of Islam.

jcr:content.jcr:title: Laws and Etiquette
jcr:content.jcr:description: Public etiquette in Saudi Arabia is informed by our cultural heritage and Islamic religion, and underpinned by values that are familiar to people everywhere: respect for others, decorum in public and protection of privacy.

jcr:content.jcr:title: Getting Here
jcr:content.jcr:description: With 13 international airports, served by a wealth of international carriers, getting to and around the Kingdom couldn’t be easier.

jcr:content.jcr:title: Getting Around
jcr:content.jcr:description: A first-rate transportation system connects Saudi Arabia’s provinces and cities, serving millions of people each day.
